# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __len__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__len__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __len__.
# len(x) delegates to __len__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types define no sizing protocol in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue size is reported via qsize()
#   method; no __len__ is defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: completed tasks carry a single result value; no
#   __len__ defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization
#   guards with no __len__ in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

